Text Count: 3771, reading time approximately 6.5 minutes

Introduction: "Wuhan Pneumonia whether person-to-person" this question, has been concerned by the outside world. Without official confirmation, public self-protection was weakened, and it wasn't until new cases emerged in Beijing, Shanghai and Shenzhen that the public began to realize that Wuhan pneumonia was not simple.

By Ma Xiaohua

On the afternoon of January 20, at a press question-and-answer session on the prevention and control of the "COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic" , academician Zhong Nanshan, head of the National Health Commission's high-level Expert Group, confirmed the "human-to-human transmission" of pneumonia in Wuhan, and had a medical infection.

By Ma Xiaohua

On the afternoon of January 20, at a press question-and-answer session on the prevention and control of the "COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic" , academician Zhong Nanshan, head of the National Health Commission's high-level Expert Group, confirmed the "human-to-human transmission" of pneumonia in Wuhan, and had a medical infection.

"It was found in about four or five provinces and cities throughout the country, and almost all of them were related to Wuhan, as if they had been to Wuhan, from Wuhan to Florida, confirming the spread of human infection. There is also confirmation of infection among medical staff,"Zhong Nanshan said.

"whether Wuhan Pneumonia is transmitted from person to person" this question, has been concerned by the outside world. Without official confirmation, public self-protection may be weakened, and it wasn't until new cases emerged in Beijing, Shanghai and Shenzhen that the public really began to realize that Wuhan pneumonia was not simple.

The outbreak is spreading. As of 24:00 on January 20,291 confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia have been reported in China (270 in Hubei, 5 in Beijing, 14 in Guangdong and 2 in Shanghai)  There were 54 suspected cases (11 in Hubei, 7 in Guangdong, 3 in Sichuan, 1 in Yunnan, 7 in Shanghai, 1 in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, 1 in Shandong, 1 in Jilin, 1 in Anhui, 16 in Zhejiang, 2 in Jiangxi, 1 in Hainan, 1 in Guizhou and 1 in Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region) . Japan reported 1 confirmed case, Thailand 2 confirmed cases and Korea 1 confirmed case.

From the discovery to the spread, from December 31 to January 21,20 days after the outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan, it is necessary to control the epidemic means and information released to do a comb and restore.

Slackening when no apparent human-to-human transmission has been observed

On December 30,2019, an emergency notice concerning the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause, purportedly issued by the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission, was circulated. According to the notice, patients with pneumonia of unknown cause have been found in some medical institutions in Wuhan, and the relevant medical institutions are required to provide proper medical treatment.

This is "Wuhan Pneumonia" appears the earliest one signal.

On December 31, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued its first announcement: Some medical institutions have recently found that more than one pneumonia case has been linked to Haixian city in south China, and 27 cases have been found, seven of them in serious condition, the remaining cases are stable and controllable, with 2 cases improving and to be discharged in the near future.

After organizing consultations among clinical, epidemiological and virological experts from Tongji Hospital, Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Wuhan Virus Institute of Chinese Academy of Sciences, Wuhan Infectious Disease Hospital and Wuhan Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Wuhan, experts from the condition, treatment outcome, epidemiological investigation, preliminary laboratory testing and other aspects of the situation, that the case is viral pneumonia.

It was the first time that it was known as "Wuhan Pneumonia"-"viral pneumonia" . And experts believe that at this time the virus did not find obvious human-to-human phenomenon, did not find medical staff infection.

"The fact that there is no obvious human-to-human transmission is important, because most of the viral pneumonia that are known to be caused by the virus are human-to-human, which means that this is going to be an unknown new virus, " said one virologist.

In fact, in this circular, Wuhan City Health Commission also ruled out the known virus. "So far, the viruses that have been investigated for viral pneumonia are commonly influenza, others are parainfluenza, Cytomegalovirus, adenoviruses, rhinovirus, coronaviruses, etc. . "

The pneumonia epidemic in Wuhan continued to develop under the conclusion of "no obvious human-to-human transmission" .

The South China seafood market has not been closed for a while.

December 31,13:00, the first financial reporter came to the South China seafood market, saw businesses are in normal operation, rarely stop shop situation, also very few people wear masks.

A businessman told the first financial reporter, the mall will do regular disinfection, not because someone got pneumonia and special disinfection.

This brief lull in prevention and control is ill-suited to the rising number of people with pneumonia of unknown origin.

On January 3,2020, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued a second notice: As of 8:00 on January 3, the city had found a total of 44 patients who met the diagnostic criteria for unknown causes, including 11 cases of severe illness, according to the viral pneumonia.

On January 5, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued a third notice: As of 8:00 on January 5, the city had reported a total of 59 cases, including 7 cases of severe illness, that met the diagnosis of viral pneumonia for unknown reasons.

The number of patients is increasing. "The preliminary investigation showed no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission and no medical staff infection, " the report concluded

As for the virus itself, the notification was unequivocal: Respiratory Pathogens such as influenza, avian influenza, Adenovirus, Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome and Mers have been ruled out. The identification of the pathogen and the tracing of the origin of the disease are still in progress.

This circular has made it clear that the cause of Wuhan pneumonia is not yet known human "new virus. ". And historically those new viruses such as SARS, Middle East Respiratory Syndrome, HIV, highly pathogenic avian influenza, etc. , are from wild animals. "The cross-species infection of wild animal virus" at this time in Wuhan Pneumonia virus tracking, in theory, has been targeted.

"The virus that causes pneumonia in Wuhan may come from wild animals, the South China Seafood Market sells game, and Wuhan is a habitat for migratory birds, and the virus can be mixed in the wild animals here, which can happen at any time, " said the virologist.

Speculation that the virus that caused Wuhan's pneumonia may have come from wild animals was confirmed in a third circular: "The closure of the south China Seafood City, and the conduct of environmental sanitation disposal and further hygienic investigation. "

Speculation is speculation, after all, medicine is a science, what is needed is scientific evidence. On January 11, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued the fourth circular, informing the public in the form of expert interpretation: "unexplained viral pneumonia" pathogens were initially identified as COVID-19.

The virus was found, the epidemic continued, and deaths began to appear.

As of 2400 hours on January 10,2020,41 cases of pneumonia with COVID-19 infection had been preliminarily diagnosed in Wuhan, of which 2 had been discharged from hospital, 7 had been seriously ill and 1 had died. The remaining patients were in stable condition, the fourth circular said. All 739 close contacts, including 419 medical personnel, have been put under medical observation and no related cases have been found.

"coronaviruses are infectious in nature, and the new coronavirus shares 78 per cent of the genetic identity with SARS, the SARS twin, which presents with severe Acute respiratory distress syndrome, as does the new coronavirus. This is the time to start similar SARS prevention and control,"said the virus expert.

At this point, however, the reporting line remains that no medical staff infection has been detected and no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission has been found.

It was not until the seventh circular of 14 January that the changes in the scope of the circular finally became visible.

The seventh notice: Wuhan pneumonia out of the door size changes

On January 14, the Wuhan Health and Health Commission issued the seventh notification: No new cases of pneumonia with COVID-19 infection, no cured cases of discharge from hospitals, no new death cases were reported, and 41 cases of pneumonia with COVID-19 infection were reported, seven patients were cured, six were in critical condition and one died. In addition, Thailand has reported the diagnosis of a case of COVID-19 pneumonia from Wuhan.

But in this announcement, the Wuhan Pneumonia Epidemic has actually begun to change: from "no visible human-to-human transmission" to "not ruling out limited human-to-human transmission. ".

"The results of the current investigation show that no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission has been found and the possibility of limited human-to-human transmission can not be ruled out, " the circular said, but the risk of continuing human-to-human transmission is lower. Of the 41 cases confirmed so far, one was found to be family gathering. The husband had the disease first, and the husband was an employee of the south China Seafood Wholesale Market. The wife denied any history of exposure to the south China Seafood Wholesale Market.

This pair of "husband and wife case" , the first financial in December 31,2019 has interviewed related patients: The husband first sick, the wife later sick.

"This family cluster of cases, there have been signs of human-to-human transmission, and severe cases in the 20% or so, we should take measures to prevent and control severe infectious diseases, " an epidemiologist said.

At this time, however, the prevention and control of pneumonia in Wuhan did not change significantly because of "family clustering" signs of human-to-human transmission and the presence of cases in Thailand.

The only change was the absence of a paragraph in subsequent circulars: No medical staff infection was found, and no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission was found.

The outbreak continues to spread. On January 20, the COVID-19 in Daxing District of Beijing and the Health Commission in Guangdong Province reported cases of pneumonia. Of these, two cases of COVID-19 pneumonia were confirmed in Daxing District and one case in Shenzhen, Guangdong.

On the evening of January 20th Xi Jinping, the president of the General Secretary of the Communist Party of China and the Central Military Commission, issued an important directive on the spread of pneumonia in the COVID-19: put the safety and health of the people first, we will resolutely curb the spread of the epidemic. Premier Li Keqiang chaired a meeting of the China State Council Executive Meeting to further deploy the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, calling for a strong and effective containment of the epidemic.

What followed was an interview with reporters by senior experts of the National Health Commission, whose leader, Academician Zhong Nanshan, confirmed the "human-to-human" transmission of pneumonia in Wuhan, as well as the infection of medical staff.

The Spring Festival travel rush has started, and the number of people leaving Wuhan has doubled. "There is no vaccine, the first line of Defense is health education and self-protection, " said a non-hubei provincial CDC official. "Then patients come to the hospital for treatment and report suspicious cases to the CDC for testing, such as confirmation, on the one hand by the hospital isolation treatment, on the other hand by the CDC to track close contacts and take measures such as isolation observation and relevant environmental disinfection. The first hurdle to finding a patient is the hospital."

Zeng Guang, a member of the high-level Expert Group of the National Health Commission, said the epidemic was in its early stages and that prevention and control measures must be strengthened to let everyone know. The Spring Festival population flow is a very important factor, hope that the crowd can not go to Wuhan, Wuhan people can not come out. This is not an official call, but some of the panel's recommendations.

However, Wuhan is now in the peak period of leaving and returning to the city. According to information released by the Wuhan Public Security and Transportation Department on January 18, the Peak Congestion Delay Index near Wuchang Railway Station and Hankou stations rose 15.3 percent and 10.5 percent respectively from the previous month The index of peak congestion and delay around Wuchang Bay station and Acer passenger terminal was up 26.3 per cent from last week and 24.8 per cent from the same period last month.

Everyone loves their hometown, and it is very common for the migrants from Wuhan to return home for the Spring Festival. According to the 2018 Spring Festival statistics released by the Wuhan Culture and Tourism Bureau, 2,328,200 people were sent in 2018.

Wuhan ranked ninth in the country in the 2017 Spring Festival "Empty City Index" released by the Qihoo 360, an internet company. The "Empty City Index" is based on an analysis of the migration patterns of 960 million users from the eve of Chinese New Year to the eve of Chinese New Year. According to statistics, the top 10 cities with the highest vacancy rate in 2018 are Dongguan, Foshan, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Changsha, Shanghai, Suzhou, Beijing, Wuhan and Zhengzhou. Wuhan's empty city rate is 48.18 percent, which means that nearly half of the population left the city for the New Year.

"The median incubation period of the virus is nine days, the current testing equipment can only serve to monitor fever patients, there is no way to identify the virus carriers, and more provinces are likely to have new cases due to population movements in the future, " said an epidemiologist.

The annual Spring Festival travel rush is coming, hundreds of millions of people or home or travel, the prevention and control war will enter the most difficult and critical moment.
